                    true,
                    'LF',
                    'RF',
                    'RF',
                    'LF',
                    'Open Position',
                    'Closed Position',
                    '["American Spin","Catapult","Change of Hands Behind Back","Change of Places Left to Right","Chugging","Fallaway Throwaway","Hip Bump","Miami Special","Shoulder Spin","Simple Spin","Spanish Arms","Stop and Go","Windmill"]',
                    '["Basic In Place","Fallaway Rock","Fallaway Throwaway","Change of Places Right to Left","Walks","Mooch","Whip (after 1-5)","Whip Throwaway (after 1-5)","Reverse Whip","Stalking Walks Flicks and Break"]',
                    'Step 1 and 2 can be repeated, known as Double Link.
When preceding Whip or Whip Throwaway: dance 1-5 of Link, turn 1/4 R over 3-5 (Man''s step 5 is diag fwd to end LF side and slightly fwd)'
